{
  "texts": [
    "Despite these advances, there is ongoing debate regarding the optimal balance between automation and human oversight in maintaining the quality and integrity of reviews.",
    "Challenges in Automated Literature ReviewsThe literature highlights several challenges faced by automated systems in conducting literature reviews.",
    "One of the primary issues is the difficulty of accurately interpreting complex, complex information and integrating diverse findings from a wide array of sources [22,28].",
    "Additionally, LLM-powered literature review itself is not immune to the generic issue of LLM hallucination in LLM generated contents [29,30].",
    "Automated systems often struggle with understanding the context and significance of studies, which can lead to the omission of critical insights or the inclusion of irrelevant information [16,31]."
  ]
}